WEBVTT

00:02.573 --> 00:04.035
DAMN.

00:04.035 --> 00:04.535
WE LOOK GOOD.

00:04.535 --> 00:06.537
I'M THINKIN' ABOUT
TOUCHIN' MYSELF.

00:06.537 --> 00:07.478
NOT IN MY CAR, PLEASE.

00:07.478 --> 00:09.780
Man: ♪ VOICE IN MY HEAD
THAT DRIVES MY HEEL ♪

00:09.780 --> 00:10.311
[STATIC]

00:10.311 --> 00:13.114
[SAME SONG] ♪ IT'S MY BABY
CALLIN', SAYS I NEED YOU HERE ♪

00:13.114 --> 00:14.545
THAT'S WEIRD.
CHANGE THE CHANNEL.

00:14.545 --> 00:18.119
ÉSTE SALE A MARIA DE JOSE,
RADAR LOVE.

00:18.119 --> 00:20.521
[SAME] ♪ AND IT'S
A-HALF PAST 4:00,
AND I'M SHIFTIN' GEARS ♪

00:20.521 --> 00:21.192
MAN, WHAT...

00:21.192 --> 00:23.023
I THINK THE DEVIL'S
TRYING TO TALK TO YOU,

00:23.023 --> 00:24.695
TELLIN' YOU IT'S TIME
TO GO TO WORK.

00:24.695 --> 00:25.596
NAH. UH-UH.
NO, NOT TONIGHT.

00:25.596 --> 00:29.130
TONIGHT IS SPECIAL.
WE ARE GETTIN' SAM LAID TONIGHT.

00:29.130 --> 00:29.730
SOCK, I DON'T--

00:29.730 --> 00:30.801
SAM, I DON'T WANNA HEAR
A WORD FROM YOU, ALL RIGHT?

00:30.801 --> 00:34.165
ONE WORD ABOUT ANDI,
AND YOU ARE CATCHIN'
THE HEADBUTTIN' OF YOUR LIFE.

00:34.165 --> 00:36.137
YOU AND ANDI
ARE TRYIN' TO BE FRIENDS,

00:36.137 --> 00:38.739
SO THAT MEANS YOU ARE
OFFICIALLY BACK IN BUSINESS

00:38.739 --> 00:40.411
WITH ALL OTHER LADIES
STARTING RIGHT NOW.

00:40.411 --> 00:44.715
WE ARE PLANTING YOUR FLAG
AT IWO JIMA TONIGHT, MY FRIEND.

00:46.317 --> 00:49.550
[SAME SONG PLAYING]

00:54.785 --> 00:59.160
♪ THE RADIO'S PLAYIN'
SOME FORGOTTEN SONG ♪

01:00.231 --> 01:04.435
♪ BRAND-NEW DAY,
I'M COMIN' ON STRONG ♪

01:04.835 --> 01:08.799
♪ THE ROAD HAS GOT ME
HYPNOTIZED ♪

01:09.300 --> 01:14.805
♪ AND I'M A-SPEEDIN' INTO
A NEW SUNRISE ♪

01:15.506 --> 01:19.750
IT'S SO HARD
TO MEET WOMEN.

01:19.750 --> 01:21.152
WELL,
YOU 2 CRYBABY BITCHES

01:21.152 --> 01:23.354
MAY HAVE DECIDED
TO BAIL ON TONIGHT,

01:23.354 --> 01:25.756
BUT I AM NOT GIVING UP,
ALL RIGHT?

01:25.756 --> 01:27.358
[IMITATES EXPLOSIONS]
HERE WE GO.

01:27.358 --> 01:31.692
JUST GOTTA JUMP-START
THE ACTION A LITTLE,
KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

01:31.692 --> 01:34.765
[CLEARS THROAT]
WATCH AND LEARN, BOYS.

01:37.097 --> 01:39.330
♪ IN THIS, BABY ♪

01:39.330 --> 01:40.501
♪ MEJOR ♪

01:40.501 --> 01:42.333
♪ GIDDYUP, HORSIE ♪

01:42.333 --> 01:42.803
OH, NO.

01:42.803 --> 01:44.705
♪ WHO'S RIDIN' YOUR PONY? ♪

01:44.705 --> 01:47.408
♪ WHO HAS A NOOSE
AROUND YOUR NECK? ♪

01:47.408 --> 01:48.479
OH, GOD.

01:48.479 --> 01:50.811
♪ CRANK HARD ♪

01:50.811 --> 01:52.143
♪ CHECK... ♪

01:52.143 --> 01:53.714
OH. HELLO.

01:53.714 --> 01:56.187
♪ WHO'S RIDING YOUR PONY? ♪

01:56.187 --> 01:56.787
WHOA.

01:56.787 --> 01:57.718
♪ IS IT TIME TO HIDE? ♪

01:57.718 --> 01:58.719
♪ OH, MAYBE... ♪

01:58.719 --> 02:01.452
AT LEAST HE HAS ONE--

02:01.452 --> 02:02.893
[LAUGHS]
LOOK AT THIS.

02:02.893 --> 02:05.726
YEAH, GOOD THING
I SAT DOWN, RIGHT?

02:05.726 --> 02:07.428
OH. OHH.

02:07.428 --> 02:08.229
YOU GUYS
ARE MULTIPLYING.

02:08.229 --> 02:10.431
♪ 'CAUSE IF YOU
REALLY ASK YOURSELF... ♪

02:10.431 --> 02:11.902
BERT WYSOCKI.

02:11.902 --> 02:14.765
BOOTIES ON THE FLOOR.
BOOTIES ON THE FLOOR.

02:14.765 --> 02:15.206
UNH! UHH!

02:15.206 --> 02:17.468
OH, I HURT MY KNEE,
BUT THAT'S OK.

02:17.468 --> 02:19.770
SMELLS LIKE BEER.
YOU EVER NOTICE HOW
BEER SMELLS LIKE BEER?

02:19.770 --> 02:24.245
WHOO! BEST
BACHELORETTE PARTY EVER!

02:24.245 --> 02:26.747
HAVING SUCH A BLAST,
HEY, NICOLE?

02:26.747 --> 02:30.781
WE ARE SENDING YOU OUT
IN STYLE!

02:30.781 --> 02:34.485
I THINK WE'LL BE SENDING
NICOLE OUT IN A BODY BAG.

02:34.485 --> 02:36.827
[LAUGHTER]

02:38.859 --> 02:41.762
THEY ARE LAUGHING
AT ANYTHING.

02:41.762 --> 02:43.163
WE ARE SO IN.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.696
[LAUGHTER]

02:51.272 --> 02:53.344
[LAUGHTER STOPS]

02:57.548 --> 02:59.750
[GIGGLE]

03:01.752 --> 03:04.855
I'VE HAD, LIKE,
7 LONG ISLAND ICED TEAS.

03:04.855 --> 03:08.219
I WAS GONNA SAY
IT TASTED LIKE A COSMO.

03:08.219 --> 03:10.821
I'M TAYLOR.
SAM.

03:10.821 --> 03:11.822
[LAUGHTER]

03:11.822 --> 03:12.723
COME ON.

03:12.723 --> 03:14.365
SHOTS. SHOTS.

03:14.365 --> 03:15.966
MORE DRINKS FOR YOU.

03:15.966 --> 03:17.528
THIS IS MY NUMBER.

03:17.528 --> 03:18.769
OK.

03:20.901 --> 03:21.802
BETTER CALL ME.

03:21.802 --> 03:24.375
YEAH. YEAH, OK. YEAH.

03:24.375 --> 03:26.537
YOU WANT ME TO--
RIGHT. OK.

03:26.537 --> 03:28.309
GIVE ME YOURS, TOO.

03:28.309 --> 03:29.209
THERE YOU GO.

03:29.209 --> 03:31.412
Sock: AW,
DON'T WORRY, MA'AM.

03:31.412 --> 03:31.842
Ben: YES.

03:31.842 --> 03:35.846
GUYS, IT IS NOT
A BACHELORETTE PARTY
WITHOUT A STRIPPER.

03:35.846 --> 03:36.987
OOH.

03:36.987 --> 03:37.948
[LAUGHTER]

03:37.948 --> 03:39.850
OH, MY GOD.

03:39.850 --> 03:43.754
SOCK, MM-HMM,
YOU WANNA BE
OUR STRIPPER?

03:43.754 --> 03:45.656
UH, NO. NO. NO.

03:45.656 --> 03:46.757
COME ON!

03:46.757 --> 03:49.700
COME ON. YOU'RE
THE FUNNY DANCING GUY.

03:49.700 --> 03:50.401
DANCE!

03:50.401 --> 03:52.263
YOU KNOW,
I AM NOT YOUR MONKEY!

03:52.263 --> 03:55.566
I'M NOT YOUR MONKEY, OK?

03:55.566 --> 03:57.338
JEEZ.

03:57.338 --> 04:01.312
BEN, BENNY, WANNA
BE OUR STRIPPER?

04:01.312 --> 04:03.574
NOT FOR FREE.
I COULD LOSE MY UNION CARD.

04:03.574 --> 04:08.279
BUT, UH, MY BUDDY SAM HERE'S
A HELL OF A DANCER.

04:08.279 --> 04:09.720
NO. NO! I--I CAN'T--
YEAH.

04:09.720 --> 04:11.452
YES.
SAM! SAM!

04:11.452 --> 04:12.423
[CHANTING] SAM! SAM!

04:12.423 --> 04:14.585
SAM! SAM! SAM!
SAM! SAM! SAM!

04:14.585 --> 04:15.486
SAM! SAM!
[LAUGHS]

04:15.486 --> 04:18.789
SAM! SAM! SAM! SAM!
SAM! SAM! SAM! SAM!

04:18.789 --> 04:21.362
I CAN'T. I--I, UH--

04:21.362 --> 04:23.794
I HAVE A TRICK KNEE.

04:23.994 --> 04:26.837
REALLY. IT DOESN'T...

04:35.476 --> 04:38.409
IT'S JUST SO HARD
TO MEET WOMEN.

04:39.410 --> 04:40.981
YEAH.

04:58.669 --> 05:01.672
WELL, LET'S SEE WHAT
THE PRINCE OF DARKNESS

05:01.672 --> 05:04.705
HAS FOR US THIS TIME.

05:05.636 --> 05:06.637
Sam: 8-TRACK?

05:06.637 --> 05:08.038
SO, UH, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO

05:08.038 --> 05:10.341
ABOUT THAT TAYLOR CHICK, SAMMY?
SHE WAS HOT.

05:10.341 --> 05:11.742
AH, SHE'S
NOT REALLY MY TYPE.

05:11.742 --> 05:13.814
WHAT'S WITH THE VESSEL?
YOUR TYPE?

05:13.814 --> 05:15.346
[LAUGHS]

05:15.346 --> 05:15.916
IS SHE A GIRL? DING.

05:15.916 --> 05:17.918
WHAT ELSE DO YOU NEED
TO KNOW? COME ON.

05:17.918 --> 05:20.751
WE JUST--WE DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING IN COMMON.

05:20.751 --> 05:21.392
WHO CARES?

05:21.392 --> 05:22.393
YOU'RE NOT GONNA MARRY
THE GIRL, SAM.

05:22.393 --> 05:23.654
YOU GOTTA GET ALL
THIS RELATIONSHIP GARBAGE

05:23.654 --> 05:24.995
OUT OF YOUR HEAD,
I'M TELLING YOU.

05:24.995 --> 05:26.357
ALL RIGHT.
SOCK, SHUT UP. VESSEL?

05:26.357 --> 05:30.330
SOUNDTRACK TO A MOVIE CALLED
LOVE, BULLETS & BLACKTOP.

05:30.330 --> 05:31.732
NEVER HEARD OF IT.

05:31.732 --> 05:34.805
LET ME GUESS. ONE OF
THE SONGS IS RADAR LOVE.

05:34.805 --> 05:35.706
TRACK NUMBER ONE.

05:35.706 --> 05:38.769
ALL RIGHT, SO I KEEP
HEARING THAT SONG,

05:38.769 --> 05:41.412
AND THE VESSEL IS
AN OBSOLETE TAPE.

05:41.412 --> 05:43.614
THIS GIVES ME NOTHING.

05:43.874 --> 05:46.417
WELL, MAYBE THE ANSWER'S
IN THE TUNES.

05:46.417 --> 05:48.979
YOU THINK
THAT STILL PLAYS?

05:58.058 --> 05:59.490
WHAT'S THAT?

05:59.490 --> 06:00.591
OH--
AH, COOL.

06:00.591 --> 06:01.392
AN 8-TRACK.

06:01.392 --> 06:03.634
WHERE'D YOU
GET THIS?

06:03.634 --> 06:04.565
I FOUND IT.

06:04.565 --> 06:06.597
YEAH, MY DAD HAD
A MILLION OF THESE.

06:06.597 --> 06:07.738
ANY GOOD SONGS ON HERE?

06:07.738 --> 06:09.700
AH, JUST OLD SEVENTIES STUFF.

06:09.700 --> 06:11.672
RIGHT. AND YOU THOUGHT
THAT YOU COULD ACTUALLY

06:11.672 --> 06:13.644
PLAY IT IN ONE OF
THE SYSTEMS WE SELL?

06:13.644 --> 06:15.706
RIGHT. YEAH, I REALIZED...

06:15.706 --> 06:17.478
ACTUALLY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I THINK MY MOM

06:17.478 --> 06:18.449
MIGHT HAVE
MY DAD'S OLD PLAYER.

06:18.449 --> 06:20.150
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
COME OVER AND USE IT?

06:20.150 --> 06:22.382
YEAH. THAT--
THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

06:22.382 --> 06:23.514
OK.
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

06:23.514 --> 06:24.615
YEAH. HOLD--HELLO.

06:24.615 --> 06:25.986
SAM?
YES.

06:25.986 --> 06:27.718
HEY.
KNOW WHO THIS IS?

06:27.718 --> 06:28.619
I D--I DO, YEAH.

06:28.619 --> 06:30.961
IT'S T--IT'S TAYLOR.
[NERVOUS LAUGH]

06:30.961 --> 06:32.593
HAD FUN LAST NIGHT.
TAYLOR?

06:32.593 --> 06:34.495
IT WAS NICE.
WHO'S TAYLOR?

06:34.495 --> 06:35.426
SO CALL ME.

06:35.426 --> 06:37.498
OK. YEAH, I--
I'LL GIVE YOU A CALL.

06:37.498 --> 06:38.569
STILL HAVE MY NUMBER?

06:38.569 --> 06:39.129
MM-HMM.
GREAT.

06:39.129 --> 06:41.001
BY THE WAY, ARE YOUR
LIPS STILL LONELY?

06:41.001 --> 06:43.904
UH, MY LIPS ARE CURRENTLY
NOT LONELY, OK?

06:43.904 --> 06:46.406
I--I GOTTA GO.
ALL RIGHT. BYE.

06:46.406 --> 06:48.839
THAT WAS MY DENTIST.

06:48.839 --> 06:51.642
OH, DR. TAYLOR?

06:52.042 --> 06:53.043
SAM, COME ON.

06:53.043 --> 06:55.415
I MEAN,
I HEARD HER VOICE.

06:55.415 --> 06:57.718
DID YOU MEET A GIRL?

06:57.718 --> 06:59.189
WE WERE TALKING
ABOUT SOMETHING ELSE.

06:59.189 --> 07:02.953
YOU WANT--YOU WANTED
A COFFEE, RIGHT? YOU WANT--

07:02.953 --> 07:05.726
LET ME GET YOU A COFFEE. OK.

07:05.726 --> 07:06.627
OK. 2 SUGARS.

07:06.627 --> 07:08.759
UH-HUH.

07:09.660 --> 07:12.032
DR. TAYLOR? SERIOUSLY?

07:12.032 --> 07:14.134
YOU'RE SUCH AN IDIOT.

07:14.134 --> 07:16.106
I MEAN, COME ON.

07:16.967 --> 07:19.109
WHOA. WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

07:19.109 --> 07:22.743
WHOA, WHOA.
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

07:25.876 --> 07:28.549
[DISPATCH CHATTER]

07:35.656 --> 07:38.228
[HELICOPTER]

07:49.940 --> 07:52.673
WHAT THE HELL IS GOIN' ON?

07:52.673 --> 07:53.704
TRAIN WRECK.

07:53.704 --> 07:56.607
SO, TAYLOR. SPILL.

07:56.607 --> 07:57.147
OH, MY GOD.

07:57.147 --> 07:59.149
YEAH, IT'S AWFUL,
ISN'T IT?

07:59.149 --> 08:00.150
THIS IS WHAT HAPPENS

08:00.150 --> 08:02.513
WHEN YOU PLAY CHICKEN
WITH A TRAIN.

08:02.513 --> 08:04.054
THE TRAIN'S
NEVER GONNA FLINCH.

08:04.054 --> 08:04.785
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

08:04.785 --> 08:06.917
WELL, COME ON OVER HERE.
SEE THIS?

08:06.917 --> 08:10.260
THAT USED TO BE A
MINT-CONDITION '73 GTO.

08:10.260 --> 08:11.622
STOLEN EARLIER TONIGHT.

08:11.622 --> 08:14.124
WHAT A WASTE.

08:14.124 --> 08:14.965
WHAT ABOUT THE DRIVER?

08:14.965 --> 08:18.028
OH, DRIVER AND
THE PASSENGER,
THEY JUST WALKED AWAY...

08:18.028 --> 08:21.902
UNSCATHED.
THAT'S BEEN HAPPENING
A LOT RECENTLY.

08:21.902 --> 08:23.203
THEY'RE BOTH SOULS?

08:23.203 --> 08:26.036
THAT'S RIGHT.
KIT AND HOLLY.

08:26.036 --> 08:28.208
2 FOR THE PRICE OF ONE.

08:28.208 --> 08:30.641
I REALLY THINK YOU
HAVE YOUR WORK CUT OUT
FOR YOU THIS TIME,

08:30.641 --> 08:33.283
BUT I HAVE
EVERY CONFIDENCE THAT
YOU'LL SEAL THE DEAL.

08:33.283 --> 08:35.846
WHICH REMINDS ME...

08:35.846 --> 08:36.687
TAYLOR.

08:36.687 --> 08:38.889
I'M NOT TALKING
ABOUT THAT WITH YOU.

08:38.889 --> 08:40.991
I WAS ABLE TO OBTAIN
SOME INFORMATION

08:40.991 --> 08:45.195
ON ONE OF HER
MANY, MANY, MANY
EROGENOUS ZONES.

08:45.195 --> 08:47.698
JUST STROKE HER EARLOBE,

08:47.698 --> 08:52.763
AND SHE'LL DO ANYTHING.
ANYTHING. [CHUCKLES]

08:52.763 --> 08:54.965
THERE IS SOMETHING
REALLY WRONG WITH YOU.

08:54.965 --> 08:57.908
WHAT? ENCOURAGING
A YOUNG MAN TO SUCCUMB

08:57.908 --> 08:59.840
TO HIS PRIMAL
AND PERFECTLY NATURAL
INSTINCTS?

08:59.840 --> 09:04.314
SHARING THE FACT
THAT TAYLOR'S IN
HER EXPERIMENTAL PHASE?

09:04.314 --> 09:05.045
IS THAT BAD?

09:05.045 --> 09:06.947
OK, OK, STOP. STOP.
ALL RIGHT, STOP.

09:06.947 --> 09:09.950
JUST DON'T MAKE HER
WAIT TOO LONG.

09:09.950 --> 09:12.623
SHE'LL BE
OUT OF YOUR LIFE...

09:12.623 --> 09:13.323
LIKE A FORGOTTEN SONG.

09:13.323 --> 09:15.756
♪ THE RADIO IS PLAYIN'
SOME FORGOTTEN SONG ♪

09:15.756 --> 09:18.729
[SKIPPING]
♪ SOME FORGOTTEN SONG,
SOME FORGOTTEN SONG ♪

09:18.729 --> 09:22.292
♪ SOME FORGOTTEN SONG,
SOME FORGOTTEN SONG ♪

09:22.292 --> 09:23.594
♪ WE'VE GOT A THING... ♪

09:23.594 --> 09:25.165
RADAR LOVE.

09:25.165 --> 09:27.638
WHAT IS THE DEAL
WITH THIS SONG?

09:27.638 --> 09:31.571
♪ WE'VE GOTTA WAVE
IN THE AIR ♪

09:31.571 --> 09:33.904
♪ RADAR LOVE ♪

09:41.081 --> 09:42.052
Sam: ONE.
Sock:
THAT WAS NOT ONE.

09:42.052 --> 09:43.784
YES, IT WAS.
RIGHT BEHIND YOU, SIR.
YOU GOT IT?

09:43.784 --> 09:47.688
HEY, ANY LUCK ON FINDING
A COPY OF THE MOVIE THAT
GOES WITH THAT SOUNDTRACK?

09:47.688 --> 09:48.859
WASN'T EASY.
THAT THING--
OOH.

09:48.859 --> 09:50.721
THAT THING'S
BEEN OUT OF PRINT
FOR YEARS,

09:50.721 --> 09:54.324
BUT I--I FOUND
A USED ONE ONLINE, SO
IT'LL BE HERE TOMORROW.

09:54.324 --> 09:56.596
GOOD. GOOD. HOPE IT
GIVES US SOME SORT OF CLUE.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.729
YEAH. LOVE,
BULLETS & BLACKTOP.

09:58.729 --> 10:00.300
IT'S A FINE TITLE.

10:00.300 --> 10:01.872
BOOBS, BULLETS & BLACKTOP
WOULD BE BETTER.

10:01.872 --> 10:05.205
YOU KNOW, THE WHOLE REPEATIN'
THE Bs THING, THAT'S CLASSY.

10:05.205 --> 10:06.036
[SAM GROANS]

10:06.036 --> 10:10.210
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
WHERE'S THE GUY?

10:11.742 --> 10:14.314
I DON'T KNOW.
I WASN'T WATCHING.

10:14.314 --> 10:16.817
PUT IT DOWN.
PUT IT DOWN.
OK.

10:16.817 --> 10:19.149
OK, I'M SORRY.
[GRUNTS]

10:22.022 --> 10:23.293
HE'LL FIND IT.

10:23.293 --> 10:25.225
HERE! HERE! HERE!

10:25.225 --> 10:27.027
MY BACK'S
KILLIN' ME.

10:27.027 --> 10:28.298
OHH. THING WEIGHS, LIKE,
A THOUSAND POUNDS.

10:28.298 --> 10:30.801
I'M HERE AT THE SCENE
OF A GRUESOME CRASH

10:30.801 --> 10:33.033
WHICH IS THE RESULT
OF WHAT MANY WITNESSES

10:33.033 --> 10:34.805
ARE CALLING A TERRIFYING
CHAIN OF EVENTS.

10:34.805 --> 10:36.767
IT ALL STARTED
AS A ROUTINE TRAFFIC STOP

10:36.767 --> 10:38.408
WHEN THE CAR BEHIND ME
REFUSED TO PULL OVER,

10:38.408 --> 10:41.311
LEADING POLICE ON
A 10-MILE CHASE AT SPEEDS
OF 90 MILES PER HOUR.

10:41.311 --> 10:45.315
THE STOLEN VEHICLE
FINALLY CRASHED HERE,
KILLING 2 PEDESTRIANS.

10:45.315 --> 10:48.879
THE DRIVER AND PASSENGER
OF THE WRECKED VEHICLE
REMAIN AT LARGE.

10:48.879 --> 10:51.722
AUTHORITIES
ARE NOT YET RELEASING
THE NAMES OF THE VICTIMS.

10:51.722 --> 10:55.956
I'M TOLD
THAT ONE OF THE VICTIMS WAS
PRONOUNCED DEAD AT THE SCENE

10:55.956 --> 10:58.729
AND THE OTHER WAS QUICKLY
RUSHED TO THE HOSPITAL...

10:58.729 --> 10:59.790
CHECK THIS OUT.
WHAT?

10:59.790 --> 11:00.260
REMIND YOU OF ANYTHING?

11:00.260 --> 11:03.293
IF YOU HAVE ANY
INFORMATION RELATED
TO THE CRASH...

11:03.293 --> 11:05.065
BOTH BLUE MUSCLE CARS.

11:05.065 --> 11:05.836
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

11:05.836 --> 11:09.369
DON'T KNOW. DO WE KNOW
ANY EXPERTS ON OLD CARS?

11:09.369 --> 11:10.901
WELL, THERE'S ALWAYS RUSS.

11:10.901 --> 11:14.404
WELCOME TO
THE WORK BENCH.

11:14.404 --> 11:17.207
WELCOME TO
THE WORK BENCH.

11:17.207 --> 11:21.081
WELCOME TO
THE WORK BENCH.

11:22.853 --> 11:25.085
AW, DO WE HAVE
TO TALK TO RUSS?

11:25.085 --> 11:25.816
GUY GIVES ME
THE SKEEVS.

11:25.816 --> 11:28.258
YES. YES, WE DO.
BUT REMEMBER,
WE'RE ALL BUSINESS.

11:28.258 --> 11:29.319
YOU SHOW ANY SIGNS
OF FRIENDSHIP TO RUSS,

11:29.319 --> 11:32.723
AND IT'S LIKE
FEEDING A RACCOON.
WE'LL NEVER GET RID OF HIM.

11:32.723 --> 11:34.194
AH, YOU HEAR THAT,
BEN?
OH, WH--

11:34.194 --> 11:36.026
NO, LISTEN TO ME.
NONE OF THIS,

11:36.026 --> 11:37.467
"MY NAME'S BEN.
I LIKE EVERYBODY.

11:37.467 --> 11:38.729
LET'S BE
BLOOD BROTHERS," OK?

11:38.729 --> 11:41.231
I DO NOT WANT
TO HANG OUT
WITH THIS GUY.

11:41.231 --> 11:42.272
HE'S EXTRA-STRENGTH
DOUCHE.

11:42.272 --> 11:45.005
HEY, RUSSELL,
NICE TO SEE YA.

11:45.005 --> 11:48.208
THERE IS SOME FINE-ASS TAIL
IN THE BENCH TODAY.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.180
YEAH. YEAH. THERE--
YEAH, THERE IS.

11:50.180 --> 11:53.243
UM, RUSS, WE HAVE
A QUESTION FOR YOU.

11:53.243 --> 11:54.284
SHOOT.

11:54.284 --> 11:56.246
DO YOU KNOW WHAT KIND
OF CAR THAT IS?

11:56.246 --> 11:57.918
'71 MALIBU.

11:57.918 --> 11:59.089
SOLID MUSCLE CAR.

11:59.089 --> 11:59.750
LADIES.

11:59.750 --> 12:00.290
RUSS.
[SLAPS HAND] RUSS!

12:00.290 --> 12:03.954
DO YOU--DO YOU KNOW
ANYTHING ELSE ABOUT
THIS TYPE OF CAR?

12:03.954 --> 12:06.857
I KNOW EVERYTHING ELSE
ABOUT THAT TYPE OF RIDE.

12:06.857 --> 12:10.300
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN
KEEPING MY EYE ON YOU THREE,

12:10.300 --> 12:14.234
CAN TELL
YOU LIKE TO PARTY...

12:14.234 --> 12:15.305
HAVE FUN.

12:15.305 --> 12:17.337
YEAH, FUN'S OK.

12:17.337 --> 12:20.941
WANNA SEE SOMETHIN' COOL?

12:20.941 --> 12:23.073
SURE.

12:24.114 --> 12:26.176
[WHISPERING]
What?
OH, GOD.

12:27.878 --> 12:32.422
THIS HERE IS
MY GIRL MANDY.

12:32.422 --> 12:35.755
SEE, SHE'S KINDA
LIKE THE ONE ON
YOUR 8-TRACK THERE,

12:35.755 --> 12:39.059
ONLY A LITTLE
MORE EXCELLENT.

12:39.059 --> 12:43.363
UM, SO, LET'S SAY
YOU WERE IN THE MARKET
FOR A CAR LIKE THIS.

12:43.363 --> 12:46.797
IS THERE A SPECIAL DEALERSHIP
YOU MIGHT GO TO OR...

12:46.797 --> 12:48.168
OH, YOU THINKIN'
OF BUYIN', SAM?

12:48.168 --> 12:53.143
YOU'D LOOK PRETTY HOT
BEHIND THE WHEEL
OF A '69 DAYTONA.

12:53.143 --> 12:54.444
OK, OK, RUSS.

12:54.444 --> 12:58.248
I KNOW THIS LITTLE,
UH, CAR CLUB.

12:58.248 --> 13:02.182
BUNCH OF COLLECTORS GET TOGETHER
DOWN AT A LOT IN CHINATOWN,

13:02.182 --> 13:03.253
SHOW OFF THEIR RIDES.

13:03.253 --> 13:06.116
MAYBE YOU COULD FIND
A SELLER THERE.

13:06.116 --> 13:07.117
YOU KNOW--HEH.

13:07.117 --> 13:08.088
HEH.

13:08.088 --> 13:09.189
WHAT WE COULD DO,

13:09.189 --> 13:11.191
WE COULD SCORE SOME VODKA,

13:11.191 --> 13:14.294
YOU KNOW, GO DOWN THERE,
THE FOUR OF US,

13:14.294 --> 13:15.425
MAKE AN AFTERNOON OF IT.

13:15.425 --> 13:19.799
YEAH. YEAH, THAT SOUNDS
LIKE SOMETHING SOMEONE
MIGHT DO. HEH.

13:19.799 --> 13:24.334
BUT I AM PULLING
A DOUBLE SHIFT
THIS AFTERNOON.

13:24.334 --> 13:25.205
AHH...

13:25.205 --> 13:26.276
WELL,
WHAT CAN I SAY?

13:26.276 --> 13:28.238
THE LADIES DON'T
PAY FOR THEMSELVES,

13:28.238 --> 13:29.880
YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M SAYIN'?

13:29.880 --> 13:32.482
[CHORTLES]
YEAH.

13:32.482 --> 13:34.985
WELL, LET ME GIVE YOU
THE ADDRESS ANYWAY.

13:34.985 --> 13:38.118
IT'S DOWN ON KEIFER.

13:38.588 --> 13:40.120
AND LISTEN...

13:40.120 --> 13:42.492
THE FOUR OF US,
WE GOTTA HANG.

13:42.492 --> 13:45.255
TOMORROW, MY PLACE.

13:45.255 --> 13:48.058
WE START WITH POKER...
[BLOWS]

13:48.058 --> 13:48.598
AND LET IT RIP.

13:48.598 --> 13:51.231
AND THAT'S GREAT,
'CAUSE I LOVE POKER.

13:51.231 --> 13:52.602
[BAM]

13:52.602 --> 13:54.264
[FALSETTO]
WE CAN'T MAKE IT.

13:54.264 --> 13:56.236
OH. WELL...

13:56.236 --> 13:57.207
RAIN CHECK THEN.

13:57.207 --> 14:02.112
WELL, WORK CALLS.
TKK TKK TKK.

14:02.842 --> 14:03.944
PSHEW.

14:03.944 --> 14:04.544
[COUGHS]

14:04.544 --> 14:05.475
SEE YOU LATER, RUSS.

14:05.475 --> 14:08.378
ALL RIGHT, WE GOTTA
GO TO THIS CAR CLUB.

14:08.848 --> 14:12.252
I'M SORRY I PUNCHED YOU
IN THE BALLS, MAN.

14:13.253 --> 14:14.424
OH, MY GOD.

14:14.424 --> 14:15.385
THIS IS JUST SAD.
WHAT?!

14:15.385 --> 14:18.228
LOOK, I PROMISE
YOU BOTH RIGHT NOW,
NO MATTER HOW OLD I GET,

14:18.228 --> 14:22.332
I'LL NEVER MAKE YOU
HANG OUT IN A VACANT LOT
AND DROOL OVER MY CAR.

14:22.332 --> 14:24.134
YEAH, WELL, YOU NEED
TO OWN ONE FIRST.

14:24.134 --> 14:27.197
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I DON'T EVEN WANT ONE NOW.

14:29.169 --> 14:32.502
SO HOW DO WE FIND 'EM?

14:34.204 --> 14:34.874
Sock: YEAH.

14:34.874 --> 14:37.347
LET'S SEE IF WE CAN
GET THEIR ATTENTION.

14:37.347 --> 14:38.248
Ben: OK.

14:38.248 --> 14:39.980
[RADAR LOVE PLAYING]

14:39.980 --> 14:41.952
HERE WE GO.
OK.

14:41.952 --> 14:44.414
HEH HEH.
RADAR LOVE, BABY.

14:44.414 --> 14:45.115
[GUYS LAUGHING NERVOUSLY]

14:45.115 --> 14:46.216
♪ I'VE BEEN DRIVIN'
ALL NIGHT ♪

14:46.216 --> 14:49.259
♪ MY HAND'S WET
ON THE WHEEL... ♪

14:49.259 --> 14:50.220
Sam: HOW YOU DOIN'?

14:50.220 --> 14:52.492
♪ THAT DRIVES MY HEEL ♪

14:52.492 --> 14:53.493
HEY.

14:53.493 --> 14:54.124
SAM.

14:54.124 --> 14:55.425
♪ IT'S MY BABY CALLIN' ♪

14:55.425 --> 14:58.368
♪ SAYS I NEED YOU HERE ♪

14:58.668 --> 15:00.370
♪ AND IT'S
A-HALF PAST 4:00... ♪

15:00.370 --> 15:02.372
SAM, HOW ARE
YOU DOIN' THIS?

15:02.372 --> 15:04.034
SONG HAS POWER, I GUESS.

15:04.034 --> 15:07.907
♪ WHEN SHE GETS LONELY AND
THE LONGING GETS TOO MUCH ♪

15:07.907 --> 15:09.909
HEY, MAN,
I HATE THAT SONG.

15:09.909 --> 15:11.681
[MUSIC STOPS]

15:11.681 --> 15:13.213
YOU GOT FREE BIRD?

15:13.213 --> 15:14.514
UH...

15:14.514 --> 15:16.416
OH. S-SAM,
THEY'RE LEAVIN'.
THEY'RE LEAVING!

15:16.416 --> 15:19.319
UH, BEN, GET THE CAR!
GET THE--
OK.

15:20.150 --> 15:23.323
THEY'RE HEADED FOR
THE PARKING GARAGE.

15:31.601 --> 15:33.163
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
[DOOR CLOSES]

15:33.163 --> 15:35.966
WE CAN TRAP 'EM
ON THE ROOF!

15:35.966 --> 15:38.708
Sock, panting:
OH, GOD.

15:38.708 --> 15:39.639
OK.

15:39.639 --> 15:41.611
UH, UH...

15:41.611 --> 15:43.613
THERE! THERE!

15:48.578 --> 15:49.519
OH, HOLY--

15:49.519 --> 15:54.324
COME ON. COME ON.
WHERE ARE YOU GUYS?

15:57.157 --> 15:59.189
[GASPING]

16:51.281 --> 16:54.144
HAVE A NICE DAY.

16:54.144 --> 16:54.744
HI.
HI.

16:54.744 --> 16:56.015
DOES SAM OLIVER
WORK HERE?

16:56.015 --> 16:59.749
UH, YEAH, HE DOES,
BUT HE HAS NOT COME IN
FOR HIS SHIFT YET.

16:59.749 --> 17:01.651
OH. OK. UH...

17:01.651 --> 17:04.524
DO ME A FAVOR. TELL HIM
TAYLOR STOPPED BY.

17:04.524 --> 17:06.796
YOU'RE TAYLOR?
YEP.

17:06.796 --> 17:08.728
WHY?
DID HE MENTION ME?

17:08.728 --> 17:10.600
UM. YEAH, ACTUALLY.
HE DID.

17:10.600 --> 17:12.662
SO, SAM,
WHAT'S HE LIKE?

17:12.662 --> 17:14.704
UM, HE'S GREAT.
I MEAN, WE'VE JUST--

17:14.704 --> 17:17.507
WE'VE BEEN FRIENDS
FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

17:17.507 --> 17:19.069
HE IS SINGLE, RIGHT?

17:19.069 --> 17:20.370
HUH? OH, UH, YEAH.

17:20.370 --> 17:22.612
'CAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW.
GUYS YOU MEET IN BARS,

17:22.612 --> 17:24.414
THEY'LL SAY ANYTHING
TO GET IN YOUR PANTS.

17:24.414 --> 17:28.778
YEAH. WELL, ACTUALLY SAM'S
NOT LIKE THAT AT ALL.

17:28.778 --> 17:31.151
HMM. TOO BAD.

17:31.151 --> 17:32.222
[LAUGHS]

17:32.222 --> 17:33.323
HEH.

17:33.323 --> 17:33.783
ANYWAYS,

17:33.783 --> 17:36.356
TELL HIM
TO CALL ME, OK?

17:36.356 --> 17:38.788
THANKS, "ANDI."

17:38.788 --> 17:41.631
HEH.

17:42.492 --> 17:44.564
WHERE ARE YOU GOIN'?

17:45.465 --> 17:48.398
I GOT A PLAN.
DON'T WORRY.

18:06.786 --> 18:09.819
ALL RIGHT, CHECK THIS OUT.
LOOK.

18:11.591 --> 18:13.263
YOU'RE SELLING RUSS' CAR?
EXACTLY.

18:13.263 --> 18:15.795
SEE, THE SOULS ARE
ALWAYS CRASHING CARS
JUST LIKE THIS ONE.

18:15.795 --> 18:17.867
SINCE WE SCARED 'EM AWAY
FROM THE CAR CLUB,

18:17.867 --> 18:19.098
GUESS WHO NEEDS A NEW ONE.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.401
PRECISELY.
SO WE SET THE TRAP.

18:21.401 --> 18:23.333
WE POST THE CAR ON ALL
THE MUSCLE CAR SITES.

18:23.333 --> 18:25.705
HOPEFULLY THE SOULS
SEE IT, AND THEY
COME KNOCKIN'.

18:25.705 --> 18:28.538
AND THEN WE
SEND THEIR LITTLE ASSES
RIGHT BACK TO HADES.

18:28.538 --> 18:29.509
ALL RIGHT, I LIKE IT.
I LIKE IT.

18:29.509 --> 18:31.581
THE ONLY THING IS THE OTHER
CARS THEY WRECKED WERE BLUE.

18:31.581 --> 18:33.583
SURE THEY'RE GONNA
GO AFTER AN ORANGE CAR?

18:33.583 --> 18:34.414
OH, MY GOD.

18:34.414 --> 18:37.247
YOU KNOW, WE DIDN'T
THINK ABOUT THAT.

18:39.219 --> 18:40.550
BAM.

18:40.550 --> 18:42.422
NICE.

18:42.422 --> 18:43.893
HOPE THIS WORKS.

18:45.255 --> 18:47.427
SO YOUR DENTIST
STOPPED BY.

18:47.427 --> 18:48.258
HUH?
DR. TAYLOR.

18:48.258 --> 18:49.699
DR. TAY--OH, TAYLOR WAS HERE?

18:49.699 --> 18:51.761
WHAT, AT THE BENCH?
WAS SHE SHOPPING?

18:51.761 --> 18:54.734
OH, SHE WAS
IN THE MARKET
FOR SOMETHIN'.

18:54.734 --> 18:55.465
COME ON. REALLY?

18:55.465 --> 18:57.807
I ONLY SAID, LIKE,
3 SENTENCES TO HER
AT THE BAR.

18:57.807 --> 18:59.869
WELL, YEAH, APPARENTLY
YOU MADE THEM COUNT.

18:59.869 --> 19:02.912
W-WAIT. DID SHE
SAY WHAT SHE WANTED?

19:02.912 --> 19:04.774
YEAH. SHE SAID
YOU SHOULD CALL HER.

19:04.774 --> 19:05.845
REALLY?

19:05.845 --> 19:07.817
YEAH. YOU GONNA CALL HER?

19:07.817 --> 19:09.749
I--I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE.

19:09.749 --> 19:11.821
I--SHE'S A LITTLE...

19:11.821 --> 19:12.782
DIFFERENT.

19:12.782 --> 19:13.723
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

19:13.723 --> 19:16.726
I--I THINK
SHE'S REALLY ATTRACTIVE.

19:16.726 --> 19:18.758
YOU SHOULD CALL HER.

19:19.789 --> 19:22.462
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

19:25.665 --> 19:28.568
MAYBE I SHOULD CALL HER.

19:38.808 --> 19:39.809
A CHURCH?

19:39.809 --> 19:41.851
ISN'T THIS A LITTLE
TOO CLOSE FOR COMFORT?

19:41.851 --> 19:47.817
NAH. ME AND THE BIG GUY
HAVE AN UNDERSTANDING.

19:47.817 --> 19:49.419
I STAY OUT OF HIS HOUSE.

19:49.419 --> 19:50.660
HE LETS ME PLAY
WITH HIS TOYS.

19:50.660 --> 19:52.862
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
IF YOU'RE HERE TO HARASS ME
ABOUT THE SOULS,

19:52.862 --> 19:55.325
I'M ALL OVER IT.
I SET A TRAP TO NAB 'EM BOTH.

19:55.325 --> 19:56.496
NO, NO HARASSING.
I HAVE FAITH IN YOU.

19:56.496 --> 19:58.798
I HAVE TO ADMIT, THOUGH,
I ADMIRE KIT AND HOLLY.

19:58.798 --> 20:01.301
THE WORLD'S
A WHOLE LOT MORE FUN
WITH THEM IN IT.

20:01.301 --> 20:06.676
IT'S THE PURITY
OF THEIR SPIRIT THAT I
ADMIRE AND RESPECT.

20:06.676 --> 20:07.837
THEY LIVE IN THE MOMENT.

20:07.837 --> 20:12.782
THE THRILL OF BEING
CAUGHT OR KILLED,

20:12.782 --> 20:14.884
THAT'S
THEIR APHRODISIAC.

20:14.884 --> 20:16.316
2 PSYCHOS IN LOVE.

20:16.316 --> 20:19.749
LOVE? [CHUCKLES]
THERE'S NO SUCH THING.

20:19.749 --> 20:23.393
I'M TALKING ABOUT
REAL PASSION, LUST.

20:23.393 --> 20:25.455
YOU DON'T THINK LOVE IS REAL?

20:25.455 --> 20:26.626
THE FRENCH INVENTED LOVE

20:26.626 --> 20:30.800
SO THEY COULD PUT
A CIVILIZED FACE
ON A PRIMAL URGE.

20:30.800 --> 20:33.633
DRESS IT UP
WITH CANDY AND HEARTS
AND CUBIC ZIRCONIA,

20:33.633 --> 20:38.608
AND IN THE END IT ALL
COMES DOWN TO ENDORPHINS
AND GENITALIA.

20:38.608 --> 20:41.571
[BELLS RINGING]

20:46.516 --> 20:48.378
SO IF YOU DON'T
BELIEVE IN LOVE,

20:48.378 --> 20:50.249
WHY ARE YOU SHOWING ME
A WEDDING?

20:50.249 --> 20:52.722
THE BREATHLESS
BRIDEGROOM THERE

20:52.722 --> 20:54.954
BANGED THE MAID OF HONOR
LAST NIGHT.

20:54.954 --> 20:57.256
I GIVE THE MARRIAGE
6 MONTHS.

20:57.256 --> 20:59.359
WHY ARE YOU TELLING ME THIS?

20:59.359 --> 21:00.029
BECAUSE I CARE.

21:00.029 --> 21:01.431
I WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY.

21:01.431 --> 21:03.533
GIVE IN TO YOUR URGES
ONCE IN A WHILE.

21:03.533 --> 21:05.765
WHAT'S THE WORST THING
THAT COULD HAPPEN?

21:05.765 --> 21:06.666
A NIGHT OF PLEASURE?

21:06.666 --> 21:10.570
I'D TAKE THAT OVER
UNREQUITED LONGING
ANYTIME.

21:10.570 --> 21:12.271
AH, WHATEVER.

21:18.708 --> 21:21.651
DON'T FORGET.
EARLOBE.

21:21.651 --> 21:23.783
[CHUCKLES]

21:26.356 --> 21:28.888
HEH HEH. SAM?

21:28.888 --> 21:30.320
TAYLOR!

21:30.320 --> 21:32.522
WOW. UH...

21:32.522 --> 21:34.594
YOU LOOK AMAZING.

21:34.594 --> 21:37.296
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

21:37.296 --> 21:39.399
OH. UH, RIGHT.

21:39.399 --> 21:41.431
I WAS--I WAS
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

21:41.431 --> 21:43.403
YOU WORK, LIKE,
2 MILES AWAY.

21:43.403 --> 21:46.536
RIGHT. I--YEAH, I WAS--
I HAD A DELIVERY.

21:46.536 --> 21:47.737
LOOK, YOU KNOW,
YOU DIDN'T CALL,

21:47.737 --> 21:51.641
SO I JUST FIGURED
YOU WEREN'T INTO ME,
AND THAT'S FINE.

21:51.641 --> 21:54.644
BUT IF YOU'RE HERE
TO JERK ME AROUND,

21:54.644 --> 21:55.645
I'M NOT
REALLY INTERESTED.

21:55.645 --> 22:01.020
NO, NO, I--I PROMISE THAT'S--
THAT'S NOT WHY I'M HERE.

22:01.020 --> 22:03.593
THEN WHY ARE YOU?

22:04.694 --> 22:08.498
I DON'T REALLY KNOW.

22:08.498 --> 22:11.060
[LAUGHS] OK.

22:11.060 --> 22:12.632
YOU'RE STRANGE.

22:12.632 --> 22:14.404
YES. YES, I AM.

22:14.404 --> 22:19.038
UH, WELL, I SHOULD
CATCH UP WITH--

22:19.038 --> 22:22.572
RIGHT. YES.
SO...

22:25.044 --> 22:26.646
TAYLOR...

22:26.646 --> 22:29.449
YOU WANNA MAYBE
GET A DRINK?

22:29.449 --> 22:31.921
TOMORROW NIGHT,
SAME PLACE.

22:32.722 --> 22:35.685
YEAH. COOL.

22:39.689 --> 22:41.831
ALL RIGHT.

22:52.041 --> 22:53.042
HEY, GUYS.

22:53.042 --> 22:54.143
HEY,
KIT AND HOLLY CALLED.

22:54.143 --> 22:56.746
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY.
COME ON.

22:56.746 --> 22:58.608
WHOO.

22:58.608 --> 23:01.380
ALL RIGHT, THE CODE WORD
IS "JAMBALAYA."

23:01.380 --> 23:02.682
I DON'T LIKE
THAT WORD.

23:02.682 --> 23:05.455
I DON'T CARE
IF YOU LIKE IT, BEN.

23:05.455 --> 23:06.716
DECISION HAS BEEN MADE, OK?

23:06.716 --> 23:08.588
YOU STALL 'EM.
I SAY "JAMBALAYA."

23:08.588 --> 23:09.819
SAM HOPS OUT FROM
BEHIND THE VAN

23:09.819 --> 23:12.662
AND SUCKS THEM
INTO THE 8-TRACK,
AND THAT'S IT.

23:12.662 --> 23:14.624
THIS PLAN IS STARTING
TO FEEL STUPID.

23:14.624 --> 23:15.064
YEAH.

23:15.064 --> 23:18.828
LEARN TO LOVE IT.
THEY'RE HERE.

23:19.829 --> 23:22.171
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S DO IT.

23:29.539 --> 23:30.510
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

23:30.510 --> 23:31.941
THEY'RE JUST
STARIN' AT US.

23:31.941 --> 23:36.446
SUPER CREEPY.
GUY LOOKS NERVOUS.

23:43.022 --> 23:44.153
HANG TIGHT, BABY.

23:44.153 --> 23:45.695
ONLY THE DUDE
IS GETTING OUT.

23:45.695 --> 23:47.497
WELL, YOU GOTTA GET 'EM
BOTH OVER HERE.

23:47.497 --> 23:48.858
I KNOW.

23:48.858 --> 23:50.700
WHAT'S UP, MAN?
HOW YOU DOIN'?

23:50.700 --> 23:51.701
HOWDY.

23:51.701 --> 23:55.805
LIKE I ADVERTISED,
1970 MUSTANG MACH 1, MINT.

23:55.805 --> 23:58.137
WHAT I NEGLECTED TO ADD
ON THE WEBSITE--

23:58.137 --> 24:01.471
YEAH. IN THE PICTURE,
IT WAS BLUE.

24:01.471 --> 24:03.473
AHEM. YEAH,
WE HAD IT REPAINTED.

24:03.473 --> 24:05.074
YEAH, WELL, WE DON'T
WANT IT ORANGE.

24:05.074 --> 24:07.216
WELL, IT'S
A GOOD THING WE'RE
AT THE WORK BENCH,

24:07.216 --> 24:10.019
'CAUSE WE GOT
ALL TYPES OF PAINT,
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

24:10.019 --> 24:12.922
UH, CYAN, AZURE--
YOU NAME IT, WE GOT IT.

24:12.922 --> 24:15.885
THAT--THAT'S A BEAUTIFUL
COLOR FOR THIS CAR.

24:15.885 --> 24:16.786
THIS CAR, YEAH.

24:16.786 --> 24:17.627
LET ME SEE THE INSIDE.

24:17.627 --> 24:20.960
THE INSIDE. YES.
YOU ARE A MAN OF
DISCRIMINATING TASTE.

24:20.960 --> 24:24.694
I CAN TELL
BY YOUR 4 BUTTONS
UNDONE ON YOUR SHIRT.

24:24.694 --> 24:28.638
SO IT'S GOT, UH,
CARPET BOTH SIDES,
WHICH IS GOOD.

24:28.638 --> 24:30.700
A STEERING WHEEL, DIALS,

24:30.700 --> 24:32.942
SPEEDOMETER
AND O-ODOMETER.

24:32.942 --> 24:35.645
UH, NEOPRENE SEATS,
I BELIEVE.

24:35.645 --> 24:36.906
GIVE ME THE KEYS.

24:36.906 --> 24:39.208
HEY, WHY DON'T YOU
GO GET YOUR LADY?

24:39.208 --> 24:40.479
GET HER TO COME TAKE
A CLOSER LOOK.

24:40.479 --> 24:41.711
SEE IF SHE LIKES IT,
ALL RIGHT?

24:41.711 --> 24:42.682
THAT'S A GOOD I--

24:42.682 --> 24:43.953
LET ME GO GET HER, AND--

24:43.953 --> 24:46.485
WHY DON'T YOU
GIVE ME THE KEYS?

24:46.485 --> 24:49.989
I WANT TO GET
INSIDE THE CAR. NOW.

24:51.721 --> 24:55.064
I--I DON'T HAVE--BEN,
DO YOU HAVE THE KEYS?

24:55.064 --> 24:57.567
UH, WH-WHAT ABOUT
PRICE FIRST?

24:57.567 --> 24:58.528
PRICE, YES.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

24:58.528 --> 25:00.870
GET YOUR GAL. WE WILL
TALK DOLLARS AND CENTS.

25:00.870 --> 25:03.102
WHY ARE YOU
SO INTERESTED
IN MY WOMAN?

25:03.102 --> 25:05.104
J-JAMBALAYA?
JAMBALAYA!
J-JAMBALAYA!

25:05.104 --> 25:06.035
IT'S A TRAP!

25:06.035 --> 25:07.106
JAMBALAYA!
COME ON!

25:07.106 --> 25:08.638
SAM, GO!
GET HIM!

25:08.638 --> 25:10.109
GO! IT'S A TRAP!

25:10.109 --> 25:11.581
GO!
GET HIM, SAM!

25:11.581 --> 25:13.512
GET HIM! GET HIM!
GET HIM!

25:17.787 --> 25:20.249
KIT!
SEE YOU AT MIDNIGHT!

25:25.595 --> 25:26.596
GO GET HER! GET HER!
COME ON!

25:26.596 --> 25:29.599
OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH!

25:29.599 --> 25:30.600
GET HER! GET HER!
SHE'S GETTIN' AWAY!

25:30.600 --> 25:33.162
COME ON.
SAM, SAM, SAM,
GET HER! GET HER!

25:35.304 --> 25:37.567
CRA--WHOA.

25:37.567 --> 25:39.809
OH, THAT WAS CLOSE.

25:40.109 --> 25:42.241
OH, WEIRD.
IT FEELS HOT.

25:42.241 --> 25:45.745
HMM. CAN SOULS BREAK OUT
OF VESSELS, DO YOU THINK?

25:45.745 --> 25:47.617
I DON'T KNOW.
NEVER HAPPENED BEFORE.

25:47.617 --> 25:50.780
KIT SAID HE WAS
GONNA TRY TO MEET
HOLLY AT MIDNIGHT.

25:50.780 --> 25:52.882
YOU DON'T THINK SHE'S GONNA
COME AFTER US, DO YOU?

25:52.882 --> 25:55.585
GOD, I HOPE NOT.
SHE SCARES THE HELL
OUT OF ME.

25:55.585 --> 25:57.326
WELL, ALL WOMEN SCARE
THE HELL OUT OF YOU.

25:57.326 --> 25:59.789
HENCE YOUR LACK OF ACTION
WITH THAT TAYLOR CHICK, HMM?

25:59.789 --> 26:03.593
HEY, I MADE
A DATE WITH TAYLOR,
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

26:03.593 --> 26:04.063
OH, REALLY?
MM-HMM.

26:04.063 --> 26:06.135
YOU KNOW, THE DEVIL
CAN SEE HER FANTASIES.

26:06.135 --> 26:08.598
MAKES HER SOUND LIKE
SOME KIND OF SEX MANIAC.

26:08.598 --> 26:11.901
INSIDER TRADING TIPS
FROM THE DARK LORD.

26:12.602 --> 26:14.103
I SO WANT YOUR LIFE.

26:14.103 --> 26:15.705
HEY, MOVIE ARRIVED.

26:15.705 --> 26:17.076
LOVE, BULLETS
& BLACKTOP.

26:17.076 --> 26:20.810
GREAT.
QUESTION IS WILL THIS
HELP US FIND HOLLY?

26:20.810 --> 26:24.353
THE OTHER QUESTION
IS DOES THIS MOVIE
HAVE ANY NUDITY IN IT.

26:24.353 --> 26:26.616
IS THAT BETA?

26:27.917 --> 26:31.320
WHERE THE HELL ARE
WE GONNA FIND BETAMAX?

26:32.792 --> 26:36.325
WELCOME TO
THE WALL OF SOUND.

26:36.325 --> 26:39.598
HEY.
HEY, HEY.

26:42.772 --> 26:45.274
OH, WOW.

26:46.075 --> 26:51.140
THIS STUFF, UH, TAKES
UP A LOT OF SPACE IN
YOUR LIVING ROOM, HUH?

26:51.140 --> 26:53.212
[CHUCKLES]
IT CERTAINLY DOES!

26:53.212 --> 26:56.986
PRO LOGIC QUAD AMP,
SWEET RIBBON TWEETER,

26:56.986 --> 27:04.954
AND A DUAL-18 SUBWOOFER
THAT'LL BLOW A CHICK'S
PANTIES CLEAN OFF.

27:04.954 --> 27:06.095
WHUHH.

27:06.095 --> 27:07.997
YOU EVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE IT?

27:07.997 --> 27:09.028
NEVER.
DEFINITELY A FIRST.

27:09.028 --> 27:13.362
HEY, RUSS, YOU HAVE
A MACHINE THAT
MIGHT PLAY BETA?

27:13.362 --> 27:15.765
BETA?

27:15.765 --> 27:17.406
ABSOLUTELY.

27:19.138 --> 27:19.638
HERE YOU GO.

27:19.638 --> 27:24.914
YOU KNOW, I AM SO PUMPED
THAT YOU GUY--

27:24.914 --> 27:27.346
SIT DOWN. SIT DOWN.
YOU GUYS DECIDED

27:27.346 --> 27:31.350
TO COME AND PARTY
WITH THE RUSS MAN.

27:31.350 --> 27:38.657
WE ARE GONNA
GET A LITTLE CRAZY
UP HERE TONIGHT.

27:38.657 --> 27:39.228
LOOK OUT.

27:39.228 --> 27:41.731
SPACE, SPACE.
AW, THANKS. YEAH.

27:41.731 --> 27:44.363
OH! THAT'S
MY SHOULDER.

27:44.363 --> 27:47.096
YEAH.
ALL RIGHT.

27:50.740 --> 27:53.743
HO HO! ENH.

27:56.345 --> 27:57.376
WAIT A MINUTE.

27:57.376 --> 27:58.247
THAT'S REAL
IMPRESSIVE.

27:58.247 --> 28:01.811
WHAT KIND OF A HOST
DO I THINK I AM?

28:01.811 --> 28:03.913
WE CAN'T JUST
WATCH THE MOVIE.

28:03.913 --> 28:05.915
WE NEED TO GET HIGH FIRST!

28:05.915 --> 28:07.456
WHO WANTS TO RIP
SOME PEYOTE?

28:07.456 --> 28:11.991
UH. RUSS,
YOU KNOW, TONIGHT'S
NOT A GOOD PEYOTE NIGHT.

28:11.991 --> 28:17.326
OH, NO, NO, NO. NO.
PEYOTE, MAN, IT MAKES
A GREAT PLATFORM,

28:17.326 --> 28:19.298
AND THEN WE CUSTOMIZE

28:19.298 --> 28:24.233
WITH A WELL-CHOSEN
ASSORTMENT OF
PARTY ENHANCERS.

28:24.233 --> 28:29.879
WE'VE GOT ANGEL TEARS,
HORSE TRANKS, JELLY BABIES,

28:29.879 --> 28:32.211
MUSKIES, HAPPY FLAKES.

28:32.211 --> 28:33.712
HAPPY FLAKES?

28:33.712 --> 28:34.413
POPPERS?

28:34.413 --> 28:36.245
YOU KNOW, RUSS,
I WAS GONNA PASS.

28:36.245 --> 28:38.988
YEAH, YOU KNOW,
I TOOK A--I TOOK
A HORSE TRANK

28:38.988 --> 28:41.350
ON THE WAY
OVER HERE,
SO I'M, UH, GOOD.

28:41.350 --> 28:45.294
GUYS, YOU SAID THAT YOU
CAME OVER TO PARTY, RIGHT?

28:45.294 --> 28:46.055
OF COURSE.

28:46.055 --> 28:46.796
WELL, OK, THEN. COME ON.

28:46.796 --> 28:50.259
I MEAN, I DON'T WANNA--
I DON'T WANNA BE
WATCHING THIS MOVIE

28:50.259 --> 28:54.433
UNTIL WE'RE, LIKE,
ROLLING 4 DEEP, OK?

28:54.433 --> 28:56.936
[TIRES SKID]

28:56.936 --> 28:58.838
DID HOLLY
FOLLOW US?

28:58.838 --> 29:02.071
[ENGINE ACCELERATES]

29:07.016 --> 29:08.978
[CAR RADIO PLAYING RADAR LOVE]

29:08.978 --> 29:11.220
YOU...

29:13.482 --> 29:14.323
WHERE'S KIT?

29:14.323 --> 29:16.886
I--I DON'T--
I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE IS. I--

29:16.886 --> 29:20.229
WHERE IS THE 8-TRACK?!
GIVE IT TO ME NOW!

29:20.229 --> 29:22.792
NAH NYING NYING.

29:26.335 --> 29:28.237
HE'S RIGHT HERE.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.813
WHOA. WHOA.

29:49.959 --> 29:53.122
THAT BITCH IS CRAZY.

29:53.122 --> 29:53.963
OH. RUSS.

29:53.963 --> 29:55.094
RUSS. OH!
RUSS.

29:55.094 --> 29:56.165
RUSS.
RUSS.

29:56.165 --> 29:59.798
RUSS, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
ARE YOU--ARE...

30:00.269 --> 30:03.302
FLUSH THE DRUGS.

30:12.481 --> 30:13.442
HEY. SO WHAT'S
THE WORD ON RUSS?

30:13.442 --> 30:15.484
OH, HE'S FINE. HE'S ALL
ZONKED OUT ON HEAVY MEDS

30:15.484 --> 30:16.515
IN THE HOSPITAL,
GETTIN' SPONGE BATHS.

30:16.515 --> 30:18.317
IT'S KIND OF
HIS DREAM SCENARIO,
YOU KNOW?

30:18.317 --> 30:19.148
GOOD.
HE WON'T MISS THIS.

30:19.148 --> 30:21.991
COVER ME ON
THE FLOOR SO I CAN
HOOK THIS THING UP

30:21.991 --> 30:23.092
AND WE CAN WATCH
THE MOVIE.

30:23.092 --> 30:24.924
RIGHT.
RIGHT.

30:25.895 --> 30:27.826
THIS WAY.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.059
OK.

30:30.059 --> 30:31.330
HEY.
HEY.

30:31.330 --> 30:33.432
OH, THIS IS
THE SOUNDTRACK

30:33.432 --> 30:35.104
YOU WERE LISTENING
TO THE OTHER DAY.

30:35.104 --> 30:36.835
WHAT'S WITH
YOUR OBSESSION?

30:36.835 --> 30:37.236
I--

30:37.236 --> 30:39.238
WELL, YOU SHOULDN'T
HAVE TO WATCH THIS
OUT HERE

30:39.238 --> 30:40.539
WITH ALL THESE
MISERABLE CUSTOMERS.

30:40.539 --> 30:41.140
[LAUGHS]

30:41.140 --> 30:43.873
UH, YOU KNOW,
NOT YOU, SIR.

30:45.174 --> 30:47.016
FOLLOW ME.

30:49.078 --> 30:51.951
HERE. GET IN.

30:51.951 --> 30:52.621
YEAH...

30:52.621 --> 30:53.482
JUST HOLD THIS.

30:53.482 --> 30:56.555
WHERE ARE YOU
TAKING ME?

30:59.188 --> 31:03.132
OH, WOW.
YOU MADE ALL THIS?

31:03.132 --> 31:03.562
YEP. MY TED-FREE ZONE.

31:03.562 --> 31:07.937
WELL, UNTIL HE FINDS IT
AND I HAVE TO BUILD A NEW ONE.

31:07.937 --> 31:10.199
OH HO HO HO!
THIS IS GREAT.

31:10.199 --> 31:11.240
I KNOW. HERE.

31:11.240 --> 31:12.902
OH. THANKS.

31:18.177 --> 31:18.507
BEVERAGE?

31:18.507 --> 31:21.310
MOVIE'S STARTED.
YEAH, HIT ME.

31:24.153 --> 31:24.513
[LAUGHS]
YEAH.

31:24.513 --> 31:27.416
WOW.
DON'T WORRY.
I GOT IT COVERED.

31:27.416 --> 31:29.188
I GUESS SO.

31:36.025 --> 31:37.396
OPEN THE REGISTER.

31:37.396 --> 31:40.499
DON'T MAKE ME
DO SOMETHING WE'LL BOTH REGRET.

31:40.499 --> 31:43.672
MY LIFE IS
FULL OF REGRETS.

31:43.672 --> 31:46.075
YOUR MAMA KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE UP TO?

31:46.075 --> 31:48.107
YOUR MAMA KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE UP TO?

31:48.107 --> 31:49.178
HEH!
WOW.

31:49.178 --> 31:51.680
YEAH, THIS IS GENIUS.
YEAH.

31:51.680 --> 31:53.912
WILL YOU GIVE ME
WHAT I WANT?

31:53.912 --> 31:56.545
I JUST MIGHT.

32:03.092 --> 32:05.654
YEAH! [LAUGHS]

32:08.097 --> 32:08.657
DID YOU SEE THAT?

32:08.657 --> 32:09.658
THAT--THAT'S NOT
EVEN THE SAME CAR.

32:09.658 --> 32:11.130
I KNOW. I WAS JUST GONNA
SAY THE SAME THING.

32:11.130 --> 32:13.332
OK, YOU'D THINK
THEY'D GET THE COLOR
OF THE CAR RIGHT.

32:13.332 --> 32:15.164
I'M GONNA
LOSE 'EM.

32:15.164 --> 32:16.265
YOU WATCH ME.

32:16.265 --> 32:18.237
HANG ON.

32:18.237 --> 32:19.068
CATCH.
NO.

32:19.068 --> 32:20.109
UPP. YOU MISSED. CATCH.

32:20.109 --> 32:22.471
STOP IT RIGHT NOW.
SERIOUS. GET SERIOUS.

32:22.471 --> 32:24.273
WHAT? WHOOPS.

32:24.273 --> 32:25.144
[LAUGHS]

32:25.144 --> 32:28.047
Holly:
YEAH! WHOO HOO HOO!

32:28.047 --> 32:29.678
YEAH!

32:29.678 --> 32:31.520
Man: HELP.
[GUNSHOT]

32:31.520 --> 32:33.252
[CAR DOORS CLOSE]

32:33.252 --> 32:34.053
I'M SCARED, KIT.

32:34.053 --> 32:36.485
EVERY COP IN THE COUNTY'S
AFTER US.

32:36.485 --> 32:38.187
WHAT IF WE GET SEPARATED?

32:38.187 --> 32:39.628
WE MEET BACK HERE, BABY.

32:39.628 --> 32:42.091
THIS'LL ALWAYS
BE OUR PLACE.

32:42.091 --> 32:43.092
OK.

32:43.092 --> 32:45.534
[STARTS ENGINE]

32:52.001 --> 32:55.044
MIDNIGHT.

33:03.482 --> 33:06.355
KIT SAID IT RIGHT BEFORE
WE CAPTURED HIM.

33:06.355 --> 33:08.987
YEP. "MEET ME
AT MIDNIGHT."

33:08.987 --> 33:09.518
HUH.

33:09.518 --> 33:11.660
THERE'S HER CAR.

33:13.762 --> 33:15.594
YOU SCARED?

33:15.594 --> 33:16.225
DOES IT SHOW?

33:16.225 --> 33:18.227
YOU'RE KINDA HURTIN' MY ARM.

33:18.227 --> 33:18.997
OH. YEAH. SORRY.

33:18.997 --> 33:22.071
GOT SOME NAILS
ON YOU, MAN.

33:23.102 --> 33:23.572
Sock: GOT THAT--

33:23.572 --> 33:26.335
[WHISPERING]
Sock, shut up. Shh.

33:28.477 --> 33:29.738
Damn it, Ben.

33:29.738 --> 33:32.211
What?

33:41.050 --> 33:43.592
Sam, do you see her?

33:43.592 --> 33:44.523
You see anything?

33:44.523 --> 33:47.596
No, I don't
see anything.

33:57.406 --> 34:00.769
HOW DO I SET KIT FREE?!
TELL ME!

34:01.510 --> 34:03.612
HEY, GOLDILOCKS!

34:03.612 --> 34:06.175
[YELLS]

34:08.747 --> 34:09.578
AH HA HA!

34:09.578 --> 34:11.820
SUCK ON THAT, SUGAR LIPS!

34:11.820 --> 34:14.083
YEAH!

34:15.624 --> 34:17.756
SAM,
WHERE'S THE VESSEL?

34:17.756 --> 34:18.457
SAM, VESSEL.

34:18.457 --> 34:21.290
OH, DAMN. I LOST IT.
I--I--

34:24.333 --> 34:25.234
SOCK.

34:25.234 --> 34:27.636
[BONE CRACKS]

34:35.744 --> 34:41.710
WHAT DO YOU THINK SHE'S
GONNA DO WHEN SHE FINDS THAT
SHE'S GOT THE WRONG 8-TRACK?

34:41.710 --> 34:42.281
KILL US.

34:42.281 --> 34:45.083
YEAH, THAT SOUNDS
ABOUT RIGHT.

34:47.756 --> 34:49.087
HOW DOES THIS WORK?!

34:49.087 --> 34:52.391
HOW DO I GET HIM
OUT OF HERE?

34:52.391 --> 34:52.761
UH...

34:52.761 --> 34:55.764
YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME
HOW TO GET KIT BACK.

34:55.764 --> 34:56.695
AH! O-OK. O--

34:56.695 --> 34:59.228
EASY, EASY, EASY.

35:02.801 --> 35:04.703
WHOA!
AHH...

35:21.850 --> 35:24.353
I THINK YOU SEE
WHERE THIS IS GOING.

35:24.353 --> 35:24.723
YEAH.

35:24.723 --> 35:28.657
YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME
HOW TO FREE MY BABY OR--

35:28.657 --> 35:29.658
OK, LOOK,
IF YOU KILL US,

35:29.658 --> 35:30.859
YOU'LL NEVER
GET HIM OUT.
YEAH.

35:30.859 --> 35:32.731
TELL ME
HOW TO SET KIT FREE,

35:32.731 --> 35:33.832
OR I WILL TORCH
THIS WHOLE PLACE,

35:33.832 --> 35:38.507
AND THERE WILL ONLY
ONE BE OF US GETTING
OUT OF HERE ALIVE.

35:38.507 --> 35:39.708
WHICH ONE OF US?

35:39.708 --> 35:41.910
WHICH--
WHAT? I DIDN'T---

35:41.910 --> 35:43.212
AAH!
AAH!

35:43.212 --> 35:44.773
AHH-HAH-HAH.
AHH-HA-HA.

35:44.773 --> 35:45.814
AAH! AH-YAH!

35:45.814 --> 35:47.616
I LIKE YOU. YOU'RE COOL.

35:47.616 --> 35:48.917
I LIKE YOUR SHOES.

35:48.917 --> 35:49.778
AHH! AH HAH HAH HAH!

35:49.778 --> 35:53.482
LISTEN, HOLLY,
Y-YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THIS, OK?

35:53.482 --> 35:55.684
L-LET'S TALK,
ALL RIGHT?

35:55.684 --> 35:57.526
WE CAN'T
LET KIT OUT,
BUT I--I SWEAR,

35:57.526 --> 36:00.189
YOU LET US FREE, AND
WE'LL LET YOU GO.

36:00.189 --> 36:01.830
[SIGHS]

36:01.830 --> 36:03.832
WE'LL LET YOU GO.
I...

36:06.865 --> 36:08.697
YOU'RE GONNA LET ME GO?

36:08.697 --> 36:10.539
KIT HAS TO GO
BACK TO HELL,

36:10.539 --> 36:11.770
BUT YOU,
YOU CAN START OVER.

36:11.770 --> 36:13.702
ALL RIGHT, YOU CAN
FIND A NEW GUY.

36:13.702 --> 36:16.945
OH, IS THAT RIGHT?
FIND A NEW GUY?

36:16.945 --> 36:19.648
YOU THINK THERE'S
SOMEONE LIKE KIT OUT THERE,

36:19.648 --> 36:25.484
ALL FIRE AND PASSION
AND DANGER?

36:25.484 --> 36:26.615
LIKE YOU?

36:26.615 --> 36:29.958
ARE YOU A TOUGH GUY?

36:30.589 --> 36:32.821
DO YOU LIKE TO GET CRAZY?

36:32.821 --> 36:36.365
DO YOU LIKE TO PLAY
WITH DANGER?

36:36.665 --> 36:39.628
I DABBLE.

36:39.628 --> 36:40.529
GOOD.

36:40.529 --> 36:42.701
LET'S SEE
HOW TOUGH YOU ARE.

36:42.701 --> 36:43.832
LOOK, NO. L-LET'S NOT.

36:43.832 --> 36:45.634
LET'S--LET'S NOT
SEE HOW TOUGH I--

36:45.634 --> 36:46.935
I--I DON'T WANNA SEE.

36:46.935 --> 36:48.807
[SOCK AND BEN SHUDDER]

36:49.338 --> 36:50.709
Sock: ♪ I--I BEEN
DRIVIN' ALL NIGHT ♪

36:50.709 --> 36:53.842
♪ MY HAND'S WET
ON THE WHEEL ♪

36:54.883 --> 36:56.815
[IMITATING GUITAR]
♪ BENH, NEH NEH,
NEH NEH NENH ♪

36:56.815 --> 37:00.619
♪ TH-THERE'S A VOI--
VOICE IN MY HEAD ♪

37:00.619 --> 37:01.590
THAT DRIVES MY HEEL ♪

37:01.590 --> 37:03.252
Both: ♪ BENH, NEH NEH,
NEH NEH NENH ♪

37:03.252 --> 37:07.696
♪ SAID IT'S MY BABY CALLIN',
AND SHE NEEDS ME HERE ♪

37:07.696 --> 37:09.658
♪ BENH, NEH NEH,
NEH NEH DENH ♪

37:09.658 --> 37:12.701
♪ AND IT'S A-HALF PAST 4:00,
AND I'M SHIFTIN' GEARS ♪

37:12.701 --> 37:14.603
♪ BENH, NEH NEH,
NEH NEH DENH ♪

37:14.603 --> 37:15.504
[IMITATES DRUM FLOURISH]

37:15.504 --> 37:20.539
♪ WE GOT A THING
THAT WE CALL RADAR LOVE ♪

37:20.539 --> 37:21.610
♪ WE GOT A LIGHT ♪

37:21.610 --> 37:23.742
AH HA HA!
♪ THAT WE SHINE ♪

37:23.742 --> 37:25.814
[SOCK LAUGHING]

37:28.647 --> 37:29.978
S-SAM!
SAM!

37:29.978 --> 37:31.720
[STAMMERS]

37:34.983 --> 37:35.854
SAM!

37:35.854 --> 37:38.327
OHH! SAM.
SAM!

37:38.327 --> 37:40.559
OH, SAM.

37:58.777 --> 38:00.048
EH?

38:00.048 --> 38:01.380
WHOO!
AH HA HA!

38:01.380 --> 38:01.750
YEAH.
[SIGHS]

38:01.750 --> 38:07.356
♪ WE GOT A THING THAT
WE CALL RADAR LOVE ♪
WHOO!

38:07.356 --> 38:07.986
♪ WE GOT A ♪

38:07.986 --> 38:09.858
♪ LIGHT THAT SHINES ♪

38:09.858 --> 38:11.690
♪ RADAR LOVE ♪

38:11.690 --> 38:14.693
YEAH.
YEAH.

38:14.693 --> 38:16.625
DINK.

38:17.626 --> 38:18.767
WHOO.
OHH.

38:18.767 --> 38:21.029
UM, THERE'S TAYLOR.

38:22.671 --> 38:24.373
YOU GUYS
CAN DISAPPEAR.

38:24.373 --> 38:25.874
COOL.

38:25.874 --> 38:26.975
ALL RIGHT.
[CLEARS THROAT]

38:26.975 --> 38:28.937
GO, MIGHTY WARLORD.
COLLECT YOUR SPOILS.

38:28.937 --> 38:32.310
LET'S NOT CALL HER SPOILS
TO HER FACE.

38:32.310 --> 38:33.742
GOOD LUCK, SAM.

38:39.418 --> 38:43.652
SO, IS THAT YOUR THING,
KISSING RANDOM GUYS IN BARS?

38:43.652 --> 38:45.754
[LAUGHS]

38:45.754 --> 38:47.325
SCREW YOU.

38:47.325 --> 38:48.056
WELL...

38:48.056 --> 38:50.759
NO. I, UH...

38:50.759 --> 38:52.801
THOUGHT
YOU WERE CUTE.

38:52.801 --> 38:55.834
DIDN'T LOOK LIKE
THE KIND OF GUY TO
MAKE THE FIRST MOVE.

38:55.834 --> 38:58.036
EXCUSE ME? I...

38:58.036 --> 38:58.967
MAKE MOVES.

38:58.967 --> 39:01.510
COME ON, SAM OLIVER.

39:01.510 --> 39:02.671
YOU HAVE TO THINK
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

39:02.671 --> 39:05.614
DON'T YOU EVER WANT
TO JUST DO SOMETHING
TOTALLY SPONTANEOUS?

39:05.614 --> 39:08.577
SOMETHING YOU KNEW
YOU SHOULDN'T?

39:20.859 --> 39:23.361
WHAT IF SOMEBODY
OPENS THE DOOR?

39:23.361 --> 39:24.533
WHO CARES, RIGHT?

39:24.533 --> 39:27.966
YOU LIKE IT DANGEROUS?
COOL.

39:29.498 --> 39:32.801
OH, SAM. THAT TOTALLY
DRIVES ME CRAZY.

39:32.801 --> 39:34.803
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

39:37.846 --> 39:40.709
UH, LOOK, UH...

39:40.709 --> 39:42.681
THIS--THIS, UH--

39:42.681 --> 39:44.653
THIS DOESN'T FEEL RIGHT.

39:44.653 --> 39:46.985
WAIT. WHAT?

39:46.985 --> 39:50.388
SAM, YOU PULLED ME
INTO THE CLOSET.

39:50.388 --> 39:53.622
YEAH. NO, I KNOW.
I DID. I J--UH...

39:53.622 --> 39:56.164
THIS JUST--THIS ISN'T ME.

39:56.164 --> 39:56.565
CAN WE--

39:56.565 --> 39:59.968
CAN WE JUST--CAN WE
SLOW IT DOWN A LITTLE?

39:59.968 --> 40:02.701
SURE.

40:03.672 --> 40:06.875
YOU REALLY ARE STRANGE.

40:06.875 --> 40:08.577
YEAH, YEAH, I--

40:08.577 --> 40:11.409
I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.

40:17.546 --> 40:18.487
I'M SORRY, SAMMY.

40:18.487 --> 40:23.992
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE
PUSHED THAT WHOLE
TAYLOR THING ON YOU.

40:23.992 --> 40:27.696
I HAD NO IDEA
YOU WERE A HOMOSEXUAL.

40:27.996 --> 40:31.530
"WE SHOULD JUST
SLOW IT DOWN A LITTLE"?

40:32.100 --> 40:34.202
HMM. YOU HEAR THAT?

40:34.202 --> 40:37.936
THAT'S THE SOUND OF
EVERY MAN IN THE WORLD
LAUGHING AT YOU.

40:37.936 --> 40:40.068
SO YOU CAME ALL THE WAY HERE
JUST TO BUST ON ME?

40:40.068 --> 40:43.512
OH, QUITE THE CONTRARY.
I FEEL BAD.

40:43.512 --> 40:43.772
I REALLY DO.

40:43.772 --> 40:49.077
I JUST WANTED YOU
TO GET THE GIRL FOR ONCE
IN YOUR MISERABLE LIFE.

40:49.077 --> 40:50.078
YEAH, I REALLY
APPRECIATE YOUR CONCERN,

40:50.078 --> 40:53.021
BUT MAYBE I'M JUST NOT SURE
THAT THAT'S THE GIRL I WANT.

40:53.021 --> 40:56.625
RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT.
YOU'RE HOLDING OUT
FOR TRUE LOVE.

40:56.625 --> 40:59.688
I TOLD YOU, SAM,
THERE IS NO SUCH THING.

40:59.688 --> 41:01.590
YOU KNOW,
I COULDN'T FIGURE OUT

41:01.590 --> 41:04.032
WHY YOU KEPT
THROWING TAYLOR IN MY PATH.

41:04.032 --> 41:07.496
IT'S NOT BECAUSE
YOU REALLY CARE ABOUT ME.

41:07.496 --> 41:08.697
HEY! UNTRUE.

41:08.697 --> 41:09.768
IT'S BECAUSE YOU'RE
TEMPTING ME AGAIN.

41:09.768 --> 41:12.641
YOU JUST WANT ME TO BE
MORE LIKE YOU, BUT I'M NOT.

41:12.641 --> 41:14.102
I DON'T BELIEVE THERE'S
NO SUCH THING AS LOVE.

41:14.102 --> 41:16.505
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
I DON'T BELIEVE
THAT YOU BELIEVE THAT.

41:16.505 --> 41:20.579
WOW. YOU KNOW,
CELIBACY REALLY
MAKES YOU INSIGHTFUL.

41:20.579 --> 41:23.652
COME ON. YOU'VE BEEN AROUND
SINCE THE DAWN OF TIME.

41:23.652 --> 41:26.484
ARE YOU TELLING ME
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN IN LOVE?

41:26.484 --> 41:28.256
WELL, PERSONALLY,

41:28.256 --> 41:34.062
I'VE ALWAYS FOUND LUST
TO BE QUITE SATISFYING.

41:34.062 --> 41:36.825
YEAH. YOU WOULD.

